mixin quick-start
  //- ***********************************
  //- HTML for the Quick Start
  .span9.quick-start-page(style='display: none;')
    .hero-unit.quick-start-banner(style='display: none;')
      h1 Quick Start!
      p the very basics of getting a Stativus Statechart up and running.
      p You will Learn
      ul
        li How to create a statechart...
        li How to create a state...
        li How to create a event in a state...
        li How to initialize a statechart once it is defined...
        li ...and more!
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step1-act(data='QuickStartBegin') Begin &raquo;
  .span9.qs-steps(style='display: none;')
    .qs-step1(style='display: none;')
      h3 Step #1: Setup HTML...
      p Create a directory put in the  
        em stativus.js
        |  create some simple HTML in a file called 
        em index.html
        |  fill it will the following code...
      pre
        | <!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd">
        | <html lang="en">
        |  <head>
        |    <!- I'm using JQuery, but you can use whatever -!>
        |    <script src="http://ajax.googleapis.com/ajax/libs/jquery/1.7.2/jquery.min.js"></script>
        |    <script src="./stativus.js"></script>
        |  </head>
        |  <body>
        |    <div id="state-one" style="display: none; background-color: red; color: white;"> 
        |      <h1>State One (#1)</h1>
        |    </div>
        |    <div id="state-two" style="display: none; background-color: blue; color: white;"> 
        |      <h1>State Two (#2)</h1>
        |    </div>
        |    <script type="text/javascript">
        |       // Statechart code goes here...
        |    </script>
        |  </body>
        | </html>
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step2-act Next &raquo;
    .qs-step2(style='display: none;')
      h3 Step #2: Create Statechart...
      p You need to create the statechart:
      pre
        | var statechart = Stativus.createStatechart();
      .pull-left
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step1-act &laquo; Prev 
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step3-act Next &raquo;
    .qs-step3(style='display: none;')
      h3 Step #3: Create First State...
      p you need to define your first state:
      pre
        | statechart.addState("#state-one", {
        |   enterState: function(){
        |     $('#state-one').show(); // Using JQuery, but you can use whatever...
        |   },
        |   exitState: function(){
        |     $('#state-one').hide(); // Using JQuery, but you can use whatever...
        |   },
        |   fireEvent: function(){
        |     this.goToState('#state-two');
        |   }
        | });
      .pull-left
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step2-act &laquo; Prev 
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step4-act Next &raquo;
    .qs-step4(style='display: none;')
      h3 Step #4: Create Second State...
      p you need to define your second state:
      pre
        | statechart.addState("#state-two", {
        |   enterState: function(){
        |     $('#state-two').show(); // Using JQuery, but you can use whatever...
        |   },
        |   exitState: function(){
        |     $('#state-two').hide(); // Using JQuery, but you can use whatever...
        |   }
        |   fireEvent: function(){
        |     this.goToState('#state-one');
        |   }
        | });
      .pull-left
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step3-act &laquo; Prev 
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step5-act Next &raquo;
    .qs-step5(style='display: none;')
      h3 Step #5: Initializing the Statechart...
      p initalizing the statechart to tell Stativus where the start state is...
      pre
        | statechart.initStates('#state-one');
      .pull-left
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step4-act &laquo; Prev 
      .pull-right
        a.eventable.btn.btn-success.btn-large.qs-step6-act Next &raquo;
    .qs-step6(style='display: none;')
      h2 Finally,
      p with everything put together it should look like this:
      pre
